Introduction
============

S.I.T is a software to identify and evaluate the caustive genetic variants underlying a QTL/GWAS defined association region.


Requirements
============

1). Python 2, Python 2.7.x or newer 

2). R version 2.15.1 or higher

3). biopython 1.65 or higher


Installation
============

1). The R library "biomaRt" need to be installed before running sit.

To install "biomaRt" package, start R and enter:

source("http://bioconductor.org/biocLite.R")

biocLite("biomaRt")

The R library "RCurl" may also need to be installed in some case.

To install "RCurl" package, start R and enter:

install.packages("RCurl")

2). Biopython package need to be installed before running sit.

To install biopython on mac, see link: http://biopython.org/wiki/Download  

To install biopython on Linux, please open terminal and type:

sudo apt-get install python-biopython


How to run ?
============

To run S.I.T, go to " %SIT_HOME/bin/ " folder and double click "sit"

or open the terminal, enter to the directory " %SIT_HOME/bin/ " and type:

python sit

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The example input data are provided in directory "/$SIT_HOME/example/"

